title: Seth Davis: Kentucky 'not mature enough' to win title
text:
Seth Davis: Kentucky 'not mature enough' to win title Can Kentucky take the title this year? One college basketball analyst thinks it's "highly unlikely." Slot to Kentucky Links Kentucky showed off its defending chops in the first half against Alabama. And while the Wildcats’ defense fell off in the second, it might have provided a glimpse into how Kentucky can take a step forward heading into March. But will that be enough? According to Sports Illustrated analyst Seth Davis, it won’t be. During a Twitter Q/A session, Davis was asked about whether Kentucky could improve defensively and make a run at the title. 
wouldn't rule it out obviously but it's highly unlikely. Just not mature enough. https://t.co/lapMpFJO7L — Seth Davis (@SethDavisHoops) February 14, 2017 Is Kentucky “mature enough” to make a March run? The Wildcats’ relative youth didn’t seem to hurt them against another projected tourney favorite in North Carolina, a much more experienced squad. Author
